procedures.name: Blood Draw

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), and screening (HIV, hepatitis B and C).

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for various tests including urinalysis, drug screen, pregnancy tests, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum content measurement.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for the measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems, performed at specified study timepoints.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: ALXN1840 Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets, 15 mg or 30 mg, once daily.

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatments.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring, detection, and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Urinalysis

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of urine for diagnostic purposes.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including recording weight and time of each bowel movement.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: IV Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access, not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
